! conclusion:
  if you want flexible external IDs but also unique identity, coerce to UUIDs and reject duplicate external mappings before write

  + context: futon1 enforced UUID IDs and external-id uniqueness to prevent duplicates.
  + IF:
    you want flexible external identifiers for integration

  + HOWEVER:
    you also need a single identity per entity

  + THEN:
    accept external IDs only through a unique mapping and require UUIDs as the stored identity

  + BECAUSE:
    ambiguous externals created duplicate entities and long-term drift

